# .gitignore
#
# Files listed here are INVISIBLE to Git.
# They exist on your machine but never go to GitHub.

# ── SECRETS — most important ──────────────────────────────────
.env
.env.local
.env.production

# ── BUILD OUTPUT ──────────────────────────────────────────────
# /dist is generated by Vite on every build.
# Netlify runs the build itself, so we don't commit /dist.
# This keeps your repo clean — only SOURCE code lives here.
dist/

# ── DEPENDENCIES ──────────────────────────────────────────────
# node_modules can be 200MB+. Never commit it.
# Anyone cloning the repo runs "npm install" to get them back.
node_modules/

# ── OS / EDITOR JUNK ──────────────────────────────────────────
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
.vscode/settings.json
*.log
